[
    {
        "index": 1,
        "start_time": 6595,
        "end_time": 8120,
        "text": "To understand climate change,"
    },
    {
        "index": 2,
        "start_time": 8120,
        "end_time": 9844,
        "text": "think of the game &quot;Tetris.&quot;"
    },
    {
        "index": 3,
        "start_time": 9844,
        "end_time": 14262,
        "text": "For eons, Earth has played a version of this game with blocks of carbon."
    },
    {
        "index": 4,
        "start_time": 14262,
        "end_time": 17797,
        "text": "They enter the atmosphere as carbon dioxide gas from volcanoes,"
    },
    {
        "index": 5,
        "start_time": 17797,
        "end_time": 19343,
        "text": "decaying plant matter,"
    },
    {
        "index": 6,
        "start_time": 19343,
        "end_time": 20510,
        "text": "breathing creatures"
    },
    {
        "index": 7,
        "start_time": 20510,
        "end_time": 21968,
        "text": "and the surface of the sea."
    },
    {
        "index": 8,
        "start_time": 21968,
        "end_time": 25888,
        "text": "And they leave the atmosphere when they&#39;re used by plants during photosynthesis,"
    },
    {
        "index": 9,
        "start_time": 25888,
        "end_time": 27512,
        "text": "absorbed back into the ocean,"
    },
    {
        "index": 10,
        "start_time": 27512,
        "end_time": 29677,
        "text": "or stored in soil and sediment."
    },
    {
        "index": 11,
        "start_time": 29677,
        "end_time": 32179,
        "text": "This game of Tetris is called the carbon cycle,"
    },
    {
        "index": 12,
        "start_time": 32179,
        "end_time": 34682,
        "text": "and it&#39;s the engine of life on Earth."
    },
    {
        "index": 13,
        "start_time": 34682,
        "end_time": 36761,
        "text": "What&#39;s the connection to climate?"
    },
    {
        "index": 14,
        "start_time": 36761,
        "end_time": 39177,
        "text": "Well, when that carbon dioxide is in the air,"
    },
    {
        "index": 15,
        "start_time": 39177,
        "end_time": 40820,
        "text": "waiting to be reabsorbed,"
    },
    {
        "index": 16,
        "start_time": 40820,
        "end_time": 42705,
        "text": "it traps a portion of the sun&#39;s heat,"
    },
    {
        "index": 17,
        "start_time": 42705,
        "end_time": 44844,
        "text": "which would otherwise escape to space."
    },
    {
        "index": 18,
        "start_time": 44844,
        "end_time": 47786,
        "text": "That&#39;s why carbon dioxide is called a greenhouse gas."
    },
    {
        "index": 19,
        "start_time": 47786,
        "end_time": 49579,
        "text": "It creates a blanket of warmth,"
    },
    {
        "index": 20,
        "start_time": 49579,
        "end_time": 51261,
        "text": "known as the greenhouse effect,"
    },
    {
        "index": 21,
        "start_time": 51261,
        "end_time": 53929,
        "text": "that keeps our Earth from freezing like Mars."
    },
    {
        "index": 22,
        "start_time": 53929,
        "end_time": 57793,
        "text": "The more carbon dioxide blocks hang out in the atmosphere waiting to be cleared,"
    },
    {
        "index": 23,
        "start_time": 57793,
        "end_time": 59796,
        "text": "the warmer Earth becomes."
    },
    {
        "index": 24,
        "start_time": 59796,
        "end_time": 61881,
        "text": "Though the amount of carbon in the atmosphere"
    },
    {
        "index": 25,
        "start_time": 61881,
        "end_time": 65013,
        "text": "has varied through ice ages and astroid impacts,"
    },
    {
        "index": 26,
        "start_time": 65013,
        "end_time": 69262,
        "text": "over the past 8,000 years the stable climate we know took shape,"
    },
    {
        "index": 27,
        "start_time": 69262,
        "end_time": 72141,
        "text": "allowing human civilization to thrive."
    },
    {
        "index": 28,
        "start_time": 72141,
        "end_time": 74145,
        "text": "But about 200 years ago,"
    },
    {
        "index": 29,
        "start_time": 74145,
        "end_time": 77511,
        "text": "we began digging up that old carbon that had been stored in the soil."
    },
    {
        "index": 30,
        "start_time": 77511,
        "end_time": 80845,
        "text": "These fossil fuels, coal, oil and natural gas"
    },
    {
        "index": 31,
        "start_time": 80845,
        "end_time": 83697,
        "text": "are made from the buried remains of plants and animals"
    },
    {
        "index": 32,
        "start_time": 83697,
        "end_time": 86782,
        "text": "that died long before humans evolved."
    },
    {
        "index": 33,
        "start_time": 86782,
        "end_time": 89179,
        "text": "The energy stored inside them was able to power"
    },
    {
        "index": 34,
        "start_time": 89179,
        "end_time": 91871,
        "text": "our factories, cars and power plants."
    },
    {
        "index": 35,
        "start_time": 91871,
        "end_time": 97042,
        "text": "But burning these fuels also injected new carbon blocks into Earth&#39;s Tetris game."
    },
    {
        "index": 36,
        "start_time": 97042,
        "end_time": 99845,
        "text": "At the same time, we cleared forests for agriculture,"
    },
    {
        "index": 37,
        "start_time": 99845,
        "end_time": 103466,
        "text": "reducing the Earth&#39;s ability to remove the blocks."
    },
    {
        "index": 38,
        "start_time": 103466,
        "end_time": 106730,
        "text": "And since 1750, the amount of carbon in the atmosophere"
    },
    {
        "index": 39,
        "start_time": 106730,
        "end_time": 108761,
        "text": "has increased by 40%,"
    },
    {
        "index": 40,
        "start_time": 108761,
        "end_time": 110928,
        "text": "and shows no sign of slowing."
    },
    {
        "index": 41,
        "start_time": 110928,
        "end_time": 113761,
        "text": "Just like in Tetris, the more blocks pile up,"
    },
    {
        "index": 42,
        "start_time": 113761,
        "end_time": 116736,
        "text": "the harder it becomes to restore stability."
    },
    {
        "index": 43,
        "start_time": 116736,
        "end_time": 118928,
        "text": "The extra carbon dioxide in the atmosphere"
    },
    {
        "index": 44,
        "start_time": 118928,
        "end_time": 120925,
        "text": "accelerates the greenhouse effect"
    },
    {
        "index": 45,
        "start_time": 120925,
        "end_time": 123109,
        "text": "by trapping more heat near the surface"
    },
    {
        "index": 46,
        "start_time": 123109,
        "end_time": 125823,
        "text": "and causing polar ice caps to melt."
    },
    {
        "index": 47,
        "start_time": 125823,
        "end_time": 129032,
        "text": "And the more they melt, the less sunlight they&#39;re able to reflect,"
    },
    {
        "index": 48,
        "start_time": 129032,
        "end_time": 132009,
        "text": "making the oceans warm even faster."
    },
    {
        "index": 49,
        "start_time": 132009,
        "end_time": 135540,
        "text": "Sea levels rise, coastal populations are threatened with flooding,"
    },
    {
        "index": 50,
        "start_time": 135540,
        "end_time": 137841,
        "text": "natural ecosystems are disrupted,"
    },
    {
        "index": 51,
        "start_time": 137841,
        "end_time": 141425,
        "text": "and the weather becomes more extreme over time."
    },
    {
        "index": 52,
        "start_time": 141425,
        "end_time": 145005,
        "text": "Climate change may effect different people and places in different ways."
    },
    {
        "index": 53,
        "start_time": 145005,
        "end_time": 148552,
        "text": "But, ultimately, it&#39;s a game that we&#39;re all stuck playing."
    },
    {
        "index": 54,
        "start_time": 148552,
        "end_time": 150053,
        "text": "And unlike in Tetris,"
    },
    {
        "index": 55,
        "start_time": 150053,
        "end_time": 152975,
        "text": "we won&#39;t get a chance to start over and try again."
    }
]